	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=492831"><span id="Scholar">Komzur</span></a><br /><b><span id="Scholar">Scholar</span></b><br /><span id="notbold">63 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.18]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>Here's some CLarity for you all;<br/> <br/>Item effects are checked in order of SLOT not by level of effect.&nbsp;&nbsp;<br/><br/>What does it mean?  There is a sequential order to which all effects are checked, as an example i will use this;<br/><br/>Equip one Black Alloy Medallion (Mana Preservation 2)and One Rotting Murkglider Drape (Mana Preservation 3) You will see the Focus effect in text when you cast a spell; Your Black Alloy Medallion begins to glow.. The Rotting Murkglider Drape will not take effect, because the sequence of slot checks the Neck slot before the Back slot.  <br/><br/>Summary; If you equip two haste items, whichever is in the first slot to be checked in the sequence will take effect, regardless of if it is more or less powerful than the other item equipped.  I don't know the sequence by slot yet, so if anyone has that information please add it to another post, or I will try to remember to update this one : )<br/><br/>Komzur Nocht, 59th Shin Paladin of Marr<br/>Dordan Bitroggen, 59th Kor Cleric of Marr<br/>&lt;Elite Voices&gt;</p>&nbsp;<br /><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br />Shin Komzur Nocht, Kor Dordan Bitroggen, Yun Jeck Samboo, Tenga Muru <br/>&lt;Elite Voices&gt;<br/>Maelin Starpyre</td></tr>
